 According to information, Antonio Mario Bowers (61) was last seen on Saturday at 05:45. He left his house without telling anyone where he was going.
Mr Bowers drives a silver/grey S500 Mercedes Benz. His vehicle was last seen at the Diamond Hill Toll Plaza, travelling in the direction of Johannesburg.
He is described as a man of medium built with black and grey hair and dark brown eyes. He is 1,86 metres tall and weighs 106 kg. •If anyone has seen Mr Bower or know where he is, they are requested to contact their nearest police station, or members of the SA Community Crime Watch, Maureen Scheepers on 082 565 6770 or David Wessels on 072 777 3012. •A missing persons report has been filed with the Middelburg Police who can be contacted on 013 249 1600.  VIDEO: Crowd shouts, “Juju-Juju” at public hearing about land expropriation Leser foto’s: Dis bibberend koud in Middelburg PHOTOS and VIDEO: Fire destroys Little Elephant  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za